# Amazon Sales Dashboard

## Overview
This Power BI dashboard provides comprehensive analytics and insights for Amazon sellers, enabling data-driven decision making and business performance monitoring. The dashboard integrates various Amazon Seller Central data sources to deliver actionable insights about sales, inventory, and customer behavior.

## Features

### 1. Sales Analytics
- Real-time sales tracking
- Revenue analysis by product and category
- Sales trends and forecasting
- Order volume monitoring
- Average order value tracking

### 2. Product Performance
- Best-selling products analysis
- Product ranking tracking
- Inventory level monitoring
- Stock-out rate analysis
- Product category performance

### 3. Financial Metrics
- Gross and net profit analysis
- Amazon fee breakdown
- Advertising cost tracking
- ROI calculation
- Profit margin analysis

### 4. Customer Insights
- Customer review analysis
- Return rate tracking
- Customer feedback scores
- Repeat purchase analysis
- Customer satisfaction metrics

## Data Sources
- Amazon Seller Central API
- Order reports
- Inventory reports
- Financial reports
- Customer feedback data

## Technical Implementation
- Built using Power BI
- DAX calculations for custom metrics
- Automated data refresh
- Interactive visualizations
- Custom filtering and drill-down capabilities

## Dashboard Components

### Visualizations
- Line charts for trend analysis
- Bar charts for comparisons
- Pie charts for distribution analysis
- Heat maps for time-based analysis
- Tables for detailed data views

### Interactive Features
- Date range selection
- Product category filtering
- Region-based analysis
- Performance metric selection
- Drill-down capabilities

## Usage
1. Connect to Amazon Seller Central
2. Configure data refresh settings
3. Select desired date range
4. Apply relevant filters
5. Analyze key metrics and insights

## Benefits
- Real-time business monitoring
- Data-driven decision making
- Inventory optimization
- Performance tracking
- Trend identification
- Competitive analysis

## Requirements
- Power BI Desktop/Service
- Amazon Seller Central account
- API access credentials
- Internet connection

## Setup Instructions
1. Clone this repository
2. Open the .pbix file in Power BI Desktop
3. Configure data source credentials
4. Set up scheduled refresh (if using Power BI Service)
5. Customize visuals and metrics as needed

